title: Cumiada de S. Vicente
body: It is 1000 meters above sea level and is a point from which, on clear days, both the north and south of Madeira can be seen. The road that leads from Camara de L么bos to Cumiada, passing through Ribeira Brava, was inaugurated in 1916. Near Cumiada de S. Vicente, the rare Lycopodium complanatum, a clubmoss, is found in Madeira.

S. Vicente: Parish in the north of the Island of Madeira
Camara de L么bos: Parish on the south coast of the Island of Madeira
Ribeira Brava: Parish on the south coast of the Island of Madeira

1916: Inauguration of the road that leads from Camara de L么bos to Cumiada, passing through Ribeira Brava
